Product name: Beach Bag PDF Pattern
Description:
The Beach Bag Pattern makes a generously sized tote perfect for a day at the beach, vacations, or a day of shopping.  Easy design to make even for a beginner sewer due to the variations and options.  Fully
lined bag with an interior zippered pocket, wall and smartphone pockets.  Nine total pockets on the inside.  This bag is designed with a inside size adjuster with clips that enable you to reduce the bags top width.  Left undone and you have a larger tote bag.  Magnetic snap closure and stylish strong handles.  The purse bottom has a removable insert that gives a firm base for strength.  This can be 
removed so the bag folds flat when not in use.  An easy bag to sew with a seriously professional look.  Instructions for outside cord purse tie included.
This is a PDF Purse Pattern for The Tori Beach Bag Pattern and Instructions, not the finished bag.
Finished Bag Details:
- 18" top width x 12" height x 6" depth (12" bottom width)
- 24" shoulder straps in length and 1.5" in width
- Magnetic snap closure
- Four 6" x 6" inside slip pockets
- Four 3" x 6" inside slip pockets
- 7" x 5" inside zippered pocket
This PDF download includes 9 pages of full color photos, diagrams and pattern templates for zipper placement and bag bottom pattern.  Clearly written step-by-step instructions provided.
After purchase the pattern download is immediately sent via e-mail to begin sewing right away.
Due to this being a digital item refunds and return not accepted.  Feel free to sell  your finished products with this pattern giving credit stating "Patterns by MergeBags" please.  
Please feel free to email me with any questions or comments.  Thank you for stopping by my shop!

Description:
*************************************************************************************
**Please check below sale announcement info for print description.***********
I am thrilled to announce a special estate sale, on now.  This week, I was fortunate to acquire the estate of a long time antiques dealer and picker.  This lady collected and kept everything!  There are tons of saleable items and lots of supplies and odds and ends, mostly old.  In addition, I have also acquired the inventory of an Etsy customer who has become a friend.  She is closing due to her health and I will be selling off her remaining inventory including many items she had not yet listed.  She was branching out and so there are many surprises in her boxes.
However, with the good news, comes the bad, at least for me!  My storage is full and the house is overrun with stuff.  Yesterday, we briefly lost the cat.  After we found him, asleep in a box, my wife suggested a serious sale, well she kind of insisted.  Apparantely, at worst I am a closet hoarder and at best, I have no self control and cannot say no to a deal. So, my loss is your gain.  Effective immediately, all of my shops are having a drastic sale.  I don't know how long it will go on, probably until I can see the floor in most of the house.  All items, existing and new, will be included.  I will be adding items to all of my shops regularly, I kid you not when I say there are THOUSANDS of items to add. Please check back regularly and have fun while I list as fast as I can!

Vintage Vogue Dog Poster Print, Canine Couture, 1940s  Dachshund Dog Picture Art Deco Fashion Art, Dog Art
This is an actual frameable, glossy plate from a  Vogue art book, not a reprint or reproduction. It has vivid colors on a good quality, heavy stock. 
This image was originally produced in 1947 and features a Dachshund.  It is titled: Spring Collections, Ready to Wear and is by Rene Bouche.
 
 I have matted it to fit a standard  11"  x  14" opening frame, available in many places.  This item has a new crisp white mat, pristine white backing and will arrive nicely packaged in a cellophane sleeve, perfect for gift giving.  (The overall mat size is  11"  x  14").
 This listing is for one matted, unframed print.
*********************************************************************************************************
These poses were carefully chosen by the top editors and executives at Vogue over many years.  They feature, in most cases, a stylish woman and her equally stylish dog.  (In some cases, who is more stylish, the woman or her dog, is definitely up for debate.)  Styles in both fashion and dogs often mirrored current events and changed considerably over the years.  
Vogue photographs were known for their cutting edge style, vivid colors and capturing a moment in time.  Hours were spent perfecting the look, whether the cover was to be drawn or photographed.  This series of pages has a stylish dog theme.
*********************************************************************************************************
******The pictures that show 3 prints and/or framed prints are ideas for displaying and framing these posters, one at a time or in groupings.  This listing is for one unframed, matted poster, shown in the first 2 photos with its mat in position.  (Click zoom on the second photo for a close up.)
 Print will be properly protected for shipping and ships flat worldwide.
I have a variety of great  prints and posters to post.  These would work well in pairs or multiples or for a gallery style wall.  Please feel free to mix and match and take advantage of the combined shipping discount which will be automatically applied during the checkout.  (In most cases, each additional item ships for only 50 cents in additional shipping cost.)
**************If you would like an idea of combined shipping cost, just add your items to the checkout cart and your total shipping will be displayed.  The items can be easily removed or changed, you do not need to complete the purchase at this point.
Canadian buyers please note: As shipping costs vary greatly based on location, some regions in Canada may be less expensive to ship to than listed in the shipping options.  Please inquire if you would like an exact quote.
